DO YOU KNOW When we relax, the flow of blood increases around our body giving us more energy. It helps us to have a calmer and clearer mind which aids positive thinking, concentration, memory and decision making. Relaxation slows our heart rate, reduces our blood pressure and relieves tension. When you feel stress, your body responds by releasing hormones that increase your blood pressure and raise your heart rate. This is called the stress response.
